oc:kn_15494918 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing invoice numbering format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use invoice number format based on context: Year-Seq (2026-001) for general use, Client-Seq (ACME-001) for multiple clients, Sequential (001) for low volume." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Proper numbering format improves organization and audit traceability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_1b04942d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating taxes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify client region (US, EU, UK, China, Australia) 2. Apply correct tax type: US=sales tax by state, EU/UK=VAT with reverse charge for B2B cross-border, China=VAT (13% goods/6% services/3% small-scale), Australia=10% GST 3. Include required tax identifiers (EIN, VAT number, ABN, tax registration number) 4. Add region-specific legal text if applicable" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_501eafd6 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing line item descriptions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use vague line item descriptions like 'Consulting' — always provide specific descriptions such as 'Marketing strategy consulting – Q1 campaign planning'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Vague descriptions cause payment disputes, tax audit flags, and client confusion." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_615b579b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating invoice numbers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never reuse invoice numbers and never leave gaps in sequential numbering, as gaps may raise audit questions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sequential numbering is legally required in many jurisdictions and ensures traceability for tax compliance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_63af0168 a oc:AssumptionBoundary,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating skill scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill does not know specific local tax requirements, cannot file taxes, process payments, or integrate with accounting software." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Clear boundary prevents over-reliance on skill for legal/financial compliance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_735864dc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any invoice" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Collect business details (name, address, tax ID) 2. Collect client details (name, address) 3. Gather line items (description, quantity, rate) 4. Assign invoice number 5. Set payment terms and due date 6. Calculate subtotal, tax, and total 7. Format invoice with all required elements 8. Export to requested format (markdown, DOCX, PDF)" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_76c8dfd4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When user requests PDF output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill generates text/markdown invoices, not PDFs directly. To produce PDF output, use the office-mcp docx_to_pdf tool after generating the DOCX." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users may expect direct PDF generation which is not supported natively." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_940a833b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating tax amounts" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Tax calculations are estimates only — always verify with a qualified accountant before sending invoices." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Tax rates vary by locality and change over time; incorrect tax amounts can create legal liability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9da2c6c8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When invoicing EU B2B clients across borders" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For EU B2B cross-border services, apply reverse charge and include the note 'Reverse Charge - VAT to be paid by recipient' on the invoice." ;
    oc:hasRationale "EU VAT directives require reverse charge accounting for cross-border B2B services; omitting it creates compliance issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_bf7cc4a4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any invoice" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include: invoice number, date, due date, sender info, client info, line items with quantities and rates, subtotal, tax (if applicable), total with currency, and payment instructions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing required elements delay payment and may violate local invoicing regulations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_da9b9a34 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating markdown invoice output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# INVOICE

**Invoice Number:** {invoice_number}
**Date:** {date}
**Due Date:** {due_date}

---

## From
{sender_name}
{sender_address}
{sender_email}
{sender_tax_id}

## Bill To
{client_name}
{client_address}
{client_email}

---

## Items

| Description | Qty | Rate | Amount |
|-------------|-----|------|--------|
| {line_items} |

---

|  | |
|---|---|
| **Subtotal** | {subtotal} |
| **Tax ({rate}%)** | {tax_amount} |
| **Total Due** | **{total}** |

---

## Payment Details
{payment_instructions}

**Payment Terms:** {terms}
**Late Fee:** {late_fee}""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "client_address",
        "client_email",
        "client_name",
        "date",
        "due_date",
        "invoice_number",
        "late_fee",
        "line_items",
        "payment_instructions",
        "rate",
        "sender_address",
        "sender_email",
        "sender_name",
        "sender_tax_id",
        "subtotal",
        "tax_amount",
        "terms",
        "total" .

oc:kn_dc5024d8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before generating document-format invoices" ;
    oc:directiveContent "office-mcp MCP server must be available for DOCX/PDF output generation (tools: create_docx, fill_docx_template, docx_to_pdf)." .

